dialogueNodes.dialogueText: Excuse me, are you a relative of Doctor Cadaver?

dialogueOptions.dialogueOptionText: Oh wait, you already answered that, let's get back to the questioning

dialogueNodes.dialogueText: Yes! I am Sir Red Herring! The Doctor was one of my vi- I mean cousins!
A feeling gnawed at my subconsciousness, like a rat chewing on a wire, but the rat is a mechanical death rat, and the wire is my subconsciousness.
I had this feeling, that Sir Red Herring might be the murderer!
My condolences for your loss Sir, do you mind if I ask you a few questions?
Who do you think you are? You…
...Snivelling...
...Insipid...
...Nincompoop!

I then realized I had become inadvertently engaged in a bout of verbal sparring. The games purpose was convoluted, but the rules simple. String together insulting adjectives and nouns, and repeating an opponents jab results in immediate loss. I would have to prove myself to this loquacious loser.
Well at least I'm not a...
Ah ha! You violated the one rule of verbal sparring! You can't repeat an insult! Get away from me you dog!
Hah! You think you can best me in linguistics you…
...Frivolous...
…Blue Pilled…
...Pillock!
You're nothing but a...
I’ve heard better lexicographical skills from a gnat! You’re nothing but a…
...Lily-livered...
...Lickspittle...
...Loser!
That was pathetic, I will not tolerate a...
Hmmm, well-played detective. I didn’t know there was another human being in existence so intellectual as myself.
Well, technically I am an alien.
I beg your pardon?!
I said I am 'sesquipedalien'... Now if I may ask you some questions.
Oh, very well...

dialogueOptions.dialogueOptionText: What do you know of the other residents in this house?
What were you doing last night?

dialogueNodes.dialogueText: Tell me about yourself.
I'm a killer!
Of bananas I mean! I could eat them all day long! Unfortunately, I have eaten so many that if I have one more I will die instantly!
What do you know of the other residents in this house?
Which one specifically?

dialogueOptions.dialogueOptionText: I wanna ask about something else

dialogueNodes.dialogueText: Marvin Green.
The mute, my cousin rented out an extra room to him, housing being scant and all. He always has his nose in a geography book. I know the little brat never got along with him for some reason.
Timmy Cadaver.
That little hellion is a blight upon humanity. If ever there was a baby that needed kicking it was surely him! Spends all day on his computer or yelling obscenities at passersby!
Violet Cadaver.

Ah, the Doctor’s niece. That little harlot is always T-posing around wherever she pleases! Her uncle would always give her money, no questions asked! I’d be careful around her though, many suitors have fallen under her vapid spell…
How about the deceased?
My dear cousin Doctor Cadaver… An odd man, I mean who puts on a tacky jacket, hangs themself and then walks over to their bed? Still, he let me stay here until I got back on my feet.
I got on the wrong end of the crypto market I’m afraid…
What were you doing last night?
I was having dinner with the Doctor. The food was to DIE for!
We conversed briefly, but unfortunately, the Doctor didn't want to... HANG OUT! MWAHAHAHAHA!!!
And what did you converse about?
Oh, we didn't discuss anything of... 'importance'.
Doubt!
I asked about his vast wealth, but every time the subject was broached, the Doctor would get... CHOKED UP! EEHEHEHEHEHEHE!
What happened after that?
Once he had eaten the Doctor went to bed, and I retired to my room.
I was uhhh, reading… Definitely not writing.
Doubt!
Oh, you got me! I was writing fanfiction shipping myself and my cousin’s wealth!
So, you were fantasizing about Doctor Cadaver's money?
Yes, but that doesn’t mean anything! You have nothing!
Let me ask you one last question...

I knew I would have to be smart with my inquisition. Herring lives up to his name in both slipperiness and hue. I came up with a masterful plan for getting this loquacious loser to confess. A plan so perfect that if it were a painting, the Mona Lisa would appear as a childs drawing in comparison.
DID YOU KILL DOCTOR CADAVER?!
AAAH you caught me you nave! I just wanted to have enough money so I could perform tax evasion!
I am destitute, so I have no income to stow away! Do you know how embarrassing it is to be a villain who has no money to siphon from the tax base?!
You killed a man so that you could have enough money to evade taxes?
Well I-
Good enough for me, take him away!
And what evidence do you have detective?
My evidence is, I made it up!
Good enough for me.
That makes sense
You FOOL! I mean, you full-y considered my answer!
And what were you reading?
Jetpack sex erotica!
Ah, a man of culture.
I was sadly unable to pin the murder on Sir Herring, so he would have to be eliminated.
Want a banana?
